qas.question: What is unusual about the traffic between Broadway and Park Avenue South on 17th Street?

context: On 17th Street (40°44′08″N 73°59′12″W﻿ / ﻿40.735532°N 73.986575°W﻿ / 40.735532; -73.986575), traffic runs <a1_0>one way<a1_0/> along the street, from east to west excepting the stretch between Broadway and Park Avenue South, where traffic <a0_0>runs in both directions<a0_0/>. It forms the northern borders of both Union Square (between Broadway and Park Avenue South) and Stuyvesant Square. <a2_0>Composer<a2_0/> Antonín Dvořák's New York home was located at 327 East 17th Street, near Perlman Place. The house was razed by Beth Israel Medical Center after it received approval of a 1991 application to demolish the house and replace it with an <a4_0>AIDS hospice<a4_0/>.
